                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the name of King Mǝnilǝk II; a few
                           lines in the incipit page, alternating with black lines; two initial
                           lines of each section of the text; the quire mark in fol. 19r; initial
                           syllable of abbreviations (e.g., fols. 14ra, 15ra, 16ra); elements of the
                           punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; some other words,
                           e.g., wa-ʾǝmzǝ (fol. 16rb), qǝdmä (e.g., fols. 28ra, 42ra, 44va), kalǝʿ
                           (fol. 47rb), dǝḫrä (e.g., fols. 63ra, 67rb, 70rb), salām (fol.
                           76rb).</seg>
